flowRoot.flowPara: 1) Before the game starts, mix the cards and place them with the text facing down. Then all players place their piece on the "START" space. By throwing the dice, they move towards the "GO BACK" space in the center of the spiral. When a player reaches the "GO BACK" space, the player changes the direction and continues back to the "START" space. First player who reaches the "GO BACK" space and returns back to the "START" space is the winner.
2) If you land on the "?" space, take one card and follow the instructions. After that, place the card to the bottom of the card stack.

3) If you land on an occupied space, send the other player back to the "START" space (if the player didn't reach the "GO BACK" space yet) or back to the "GO BACK" space (if the player already reached the "GO BACK" space).
4) Always follow the arrow if you land on a space from where an arrow points to another space.
5) Always bounce back from the Start if you don't land on it.
6) Once you step on the "GO BACK" space, change the dirrection and go back to the "START" space.
